the fundamentals of computer networking:
WHAT IS NETWORKING?
networks are simply things connected.
network is the key term for devices that are connected together.
for example, your friendship circle:
you are all connected because of similar interests, hobbies, skills & sorts.
networks can be found in all walks of life:
a city's public transportation system, infrastructure such as the national power grid for electricity,
meeting & greeting your neighbours, postal systems for sending letters & parcels.
---> in computing, networking is the same idea, just dispersed to technological devices.
in computing, a network can be formed by anywhere from 2 devices to billions.
these devices include everything from your laptop & phone to security cameras, traffic lights & even farming.
networks are integrated into our everyday life.
be it gathering data for the weather, delivering electricity to homes or even determining who has the right of way at a road.
because networks are so embedded in the modern-day, networking is an essential concept to grasp in cybersecurity.
networks come in all shapes and sizes.
